techmeme.title: Crypto.com launches its institutional exchange service for US customers; it had closed the service in June 2023 due to "limited demand" (MK Manoylov/The Block)
Tencent unveils Hunyuan3D 2.0, an AI system that turns single images or text prompts into 3D models in seconds, and open sources it on HuggingFace and GitHub (Michael Nuñez/VentureBeat)
Netflix raises prices in the US, Canada, Portugal, and Argentina; the standard US plan rises from $15.49 to $17.99, standard with ads jumps a dollar to $7.99 (Nicole Sperling/New York Times)
Netflix reports Q4 revenue up 16% YoY to $10.2B and 301.6M global subs, adding 18.9M subs, more than doubling Wall Street estimates; NFLX jumps 13%+ after hours (Lucas Shaw/Bloomberg)
Perplexity debuts Sonar, an API service to let devs build AI search tools into their apps, with a base tier costing $5/1K searches and a pricier Sonar Pro tier (Maxwell Zeff/TechCrunch)
